    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Marbled paper where colors are mingled with a wired comb within the prepared bath, which produces "scallops" of colors, as opposed to "veins".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000031761/Dictionary of Paper (1940)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Papel jaspeado en donde los colores se mezclan con un peine de jaspear de alambre dentro del baño preparado, resultando "conchas" en vez de "venas".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Marmerpapier waarbij de kleuren in een geprepareerd bad worden gemengd met een draad, waardoor 'geschulpte' kleurvormen ontstaan in plaats van 'adervormen'.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
